                            | Friendship Scams
                    p Scammers message you via social media or networking sites such as Facebook or LinkedIn, message boards, online support groups, or online games and apps. Instead of creating a romantic relationship, the scammer will pretend to have your same likes and interests to form a quick friendship connection with you. Once the scammer feels you care for them, they will ask you for money to help pay their bills or other financial hardships. 
